article.headline: Army 77, Polytechnic 43
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Colin Harris scored 19 points, leading four Army players in double figures, and the Black Knights beat Polytechnic 77-43 on Wednesday night. Army (1-4) scored 12 of the game's first 14 points, building a 10-point lead five minutes into the contest. Harris notched four points in that spurt and added four more during a 9-0 surge that put Army on top 25-6. The Black Knights led 34-15 at the half and scored the first 10 points of the second half. Matt Bell had 13 points, while Cory Sinning and Jimmy Sewell each added 10. Polytechnic (0-3), which shot just 34.7 percent from the field and committed 22 turnovers, got 13 points from Omar Nokaly and 11 from Aboubakar Bamba. The Blue Jays used a 13-2 run to make it 46-28 with 12:51 to play, but they never got closer.
